4 A BILL FOR AN ACT ENTITLED: “AN ACT REVISING THE RENEWABLE RESOURCE GRANT AND LOAN
5 PROGRAM AND THE MONTANA COAL ENDOWMENT PROGRAM; REQUIRING A LOCAL GOVERNMENT
6 TO ESTABLISH AND FUND A CAPITAL RESERVE ACCOUNT BEFORE FUNDING MAY BE RELEASED
7 FROM THE RENEWABLE RESOURCE GRANT AND LOAN PROGRAM OR THE MONTANA COAL
8 ENDOWMENT PROGRAM; PROVIDING A PRIORITY SYSTEM FOR AWARDING FINANCIAL ASSISTANCE;
9 PROVIDING A DEFINITION; PROVIDING RULEMAKING AUTHORITY; AND AMENDING SECTIONS 85-1-
10 605, 90-6-703, AND 90-6-710, MCA.”
11
12 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF MONTANA:
13
14 NEW SECTION. Section 1. Local government requirements before funds are released. (1) To be
15 eligible to receive funding under the renewable resource grant and loan program, a local government must
16 establish and continually fund a capital reserve account meeting the requirements of subsection (3) for
17 necessary infrastructure improvements, including but not limited to improvements to water supply systems,
18 wastewater systems, irrigation systems, and water storage dams that are not part of a public water system and
19 that have a water storage capacity in excess of 3,000 acre-feet.
20 (2) The capital reserve account must be established by September 30 of the odd-numbered year
21 preceding the next regularly scheduled legislative session when the local government intends to receive
22 potential funding.
23 (3) The local government shall deposit into the capital reserve account:
24 (a) an amount equal to 10% of the revenues received by the local government from water supply
25 fees, wastewater system usage fees, or water delivery fees assessed by the local government; or
26 (b) for the owners of water storage dams described in subsection (1), an amount equal to $5 per
27 ACRE-FOOT of water storage capacity. Revenues or royalties from the production and sale of electricity, general
28 fund revenues used for the maintenance of water storage dams and other structures owned by the local
