9 NEW SECTION. Section 3. Local government requirements before funds are released. (1) To be
10 eligible to receive funding under this part, a local government other than a tribal government must establish and
11 continually fund a capital reserve account meeting the requirements of subsection (3) for necessary
12 infrastructure improvements, including but not limited to improvements to water supply systems, wastewater
13 systems, and irrigation systems.
14 (2) The capital reserve account must be established by September 30 of the odd-numbered year
15 preceding the next regularly scheduled legislative session when the local government intends to receive
16 potential funding.
17 (3) (a) The local government shall deposit into the capital reserve account an amount equal to
18 10% of the revenues received by the local government from water supply fees, wastewater system usage fees,
19 or water delivery fees assessed by the local government.
20 (b) A local government may not create any form of special district or improvement district to fund
21 the capital reserve account provided for in this section.
22 (4) A local government may expend funds from the capital reserve account only to fund projects
23 with a total estimated cost of at least $50,000.
